HEADWORD: Attitudinize
<hw>At`ti*tu"di*nize</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To
assume affected attitudes; to strike an attitude; to pose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Maria, who is the most picturesque figure, was put to
<qex>attitudinize</qex> at the harp.</q> <rj><qau>Hannah
More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Attitudinizer</ent>⟦br⟧
